              It is not inconceivable that \msCc's (and \msM's) Łagamyagahanaṃ$ 
              (`it is inaccessible because of its depth') is original and
              it is to be contrasted with Łsamuddhṛtam$ (`lofty'). One also wonders if
              Łguhād$ could be the right reading, and in what sense, in Łpāda$ b.</NOTE>
